text:
Dear comitee, dear sir or madam,
My name is Alex Dupont, I am a student here at the Rennes 2 university and I am currently fulfulling a "information et communication" degree, I am still in the first year but I truly find the subjects studied and the degree in general really interesting, and I believe that I will be successful, due to my hard work and determination. I contact you today in order to ask for a scholarship, - as you could have imagined-,  to go and study abroad for the 2024-2025 scolar year. I currently don't have any country in particular in mind, but I'd love to go in an english speaking one, to improve my fluency and my vocabulary in english. It might sound as any other request you may be confronted to but I am truly motivated. I consider my current level in english quite acceptable (I have taken the "Cambridge" exam, that allowed me a B2 level, 3 years from now) but I would find it useful for my future career to be truly billingual, I believe it opens many doors, especially at an international level, wich I am aiming at in the future. I also consider that being aware of other cultures comming from all over the world, and not to be centered on our own, is something very important too, this is the second main goal of my demand, I would like to experience something completly different drom what I live in my everyday life, and going to a different country is quite the thing.
In hope to have an answer as soon as possible,
best regards
Alex Dupont
